body.description: Title: Thermaltake PC Modding Sleeve Extension Power Supply Cable Kit (ATX/EPS/8-pin PCI-E/6-pin PCI-E with Combs) Key Features:Compatible with ATX form factor Power Supplies (Extensions Connect into factory PSU cables)Extend your Power: Each Extension cables comes in 300mm in length with black connectors on both endsAvailable in (4) Custom Color Options: Red/Black, Blue/Black, Green/Black, Orange/BlackExtension Kit Includes: (1) 24-pin(ATX), (1)4+4-pin (EPS), (2) PCIE 8-pin, (2) PCIE 6-pin with (4x) Cable Combs for EACH cableTriple-Layered Protection: protect your power delivery with properly insulated cable sleeving, insulating and certified 16 AWG cable wireHeat-Shrink-Less Design: Each cable is proper sleeved and secured without the need for heatshrink materialProduct Description: Customize your system build with the Thermaltake TtMod Sleeved Extension Cable Kit. With three-layered cable design and inner certified 16 AWG wire, the TtMod Sleeve Cable Extension Kit offers users more flexibility for easy installation as well as a clean and professional look. The new individually sleeved cables are heat-shrink free to ensure high-quality cable assembly and support for high currents in order to achieve superior performance and stability. There are four color combos to choose from – blue/black, red/black, green/black, and orange/black including cables for (1) 24-pin (ATX), (1) 4+4-pin (EPS), (2) 8-pin PCI-E and (2)6-pin PCI-E with all black cable combs for a streamlined presentation. Package Contents (1) 24-pin ATX Cable (1) 4+4-pin EPS Cable (2) 8-pin PCIE Cable (2) 6-pin PCIE Cable (4) 24-pin Black Cable Comb (12) 8-pin Black Cable Comb (8) 6-pin Black Cable Comb Support Please visit our website or search "Thermaltake Support" for any assistance.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Thermaltake TtMod Sleeve Extension Power Supply Cable Kit Product Description Customize your system build with the TtMod Sleeve Cable, which is sleeved with the heatshrinkless sleeving method and comes in three-layered design: Outer ultra-density weaving, the middle insulating layer with acid and alkali-resistance, fuel resistance, damp proof, and mildew proof features,the TtMod Sleeve Cable combo pack offers users more flexibility for easy installation as well as a clean and professional look. The new individually sleeved cables are heat-shrink free to ensure high-quality cable assembly and support for high currents in order to achieve superior performance and stability. There are eight color combos to choose from – red/black, green/black, blue/black, orange/black, purple/black, yellow/black, white/black, and rainbow – adding to the neat and aesthetic appealing of the chassis.

Features Tidy and Clean Cable Management Cable combs with rounded edges provide a professional look and easy installation. Each comb can be placed individually along the cable for proper fitment and routing. Improve overall airflow and case clutter with premium routing of each cable for an ideal presentation. Three-Layered Weaving Design By using the most stringent manufacturing procedures and standards, the insulating layer delivers perfect uniform insulation thickness to ensure easy stripping and cutting. Furthermore, all cables are built with high-quality 16 AWG wires and ultra-density cable sleeving to deliver superior electrical connection. Three-layer weaving design delivers appropriate bending stiffness for easy installation Heat shrinkless Cabling Made with premium materials, the TtMod Sleeve Cable features heat shrinkless sleeving methods and gives aesthetic appeal and excellent durability.

Vivid Multi-Colored Selections The TtMod Sleeve Cable combo pack is available in eight color combos: red/black, green/black, blue/black, orange/black, purple/black, yellow/black, white/black, and rainbow, providing a professional multi-colored sleeved cable layout. Gain a professional look with all black connectors and dual color sleeve for a system interior that stands out with color throughout. Universal Compatibility With universal standard power cable extension connectors, the TtMod Sleeve Cables are fully compatible with most PSU brands and models. Each cable is designed to fit into the “System Side” of the power supply cable to allow extension and easier routing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I needed!
reviews.reviewText: Bought these for my wife's black and blue build. I initially bought a Rosewill (non modular. Epic fail) power supply with blue LED's to run in a full ATX case. Unfortunately, due to the size of the case, there was a lot of strain on the cables and the lack of length for cable management made the inside of the case look like a ketchup and mustard nightmare. After all the money i spent on trying to build her a high end and aesthetically pleasing build, i wasn't happy. Then i found these. While it took me some time to get these routed properly and tamed with the combs (be patient, you will be rewarded), i couldn't be happier with the end result. it really cleaned up the case and now it's looking like the showpiece I had planned in my head. Great product, quality feel and look.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 30, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These extensions are fantastic!
reviews.reviewText: This was my first set of sleeved cables and really didn't know what to expect. I'll be the first to say that these things are really great! I helped my friend do his first build and I really wanted to make it special for him. I bought this and some Thermaltake Riing fans as they were pretty much the coolest orange fans and cables that I could find. The results are stunning! These cables are the stiff kind, but I found them to be really easy to work with. The included cable combs are great and easy to snap on to the cables. The orange is quite vibrant and is very noticeable in a case. The black cabling included with the Corsair PSU that we used are very nice, but this kit really took my friend's PC to the next level aesthetically. I would definitely purchase these extensions again, given the right opportunity.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 17, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent built and visual quality
reviews.reviewText: These are exactly what I was looking for. Having just completed my build I was simply wanting too add a little flair to my new PC. Having invested in some RGB fans for my new case and to accent my GPU’s RGB elements I went with the Pink/Black thermaltake sleeved extension cables. The are thick and hold shape very well and come with ample combs for added management. I would recommend these to anyone looking for some nice extension/accent cables for their PC.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful, and oh so extra. (SLI users be warned)
reviews.reviewText: Absolutely the perfect addition to any colorful build. I'm fully Strix'd out so I have enough RGB's to make a Porygon jealous, and I wasn't a big fan of the cables that came with my power supply. These cables are perfect. They're very brightly colored and clearly high quality. I was a little disappointed for $50 they only come with 2 8 pin extensions, and as far as I can tell the only way for me to get more is but another set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars They look and feel great!
reviews.reviewText: They look a lot better in real life and the extensions feel very high quality. The packaging was really neat and installation is straightforward. However, these cables are a bit fat and are an extremely tight fit within an NZXT comb. Extreme amounts of pressure is needed to force them in place if you have an NZXT cable comb. My fingers are pretty raw and bruised, yet the results were well worth it. They are also pretty long so the smaller your case is the more trouble you'll have hiding them. Would definitely recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 26, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good sleeved extension cables
reviews.reviewText: These are well constructed extensions with top notch sleeveing. The wire is stiffer and as a result has a wider curve radius than a flimsier wire would but I think it gives a better look to the system build. These are extensions so the extra cable will have to be tucked away somewhere and that's the only detraction from a completely sleeved cable set. The included cable combs are sturdy yet pliable and none broke when I was placing them on the cables and then redoing them when I changed graphics cards and had to add the second eight pin cable to the mix.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Just can't give them five stars.. read on to find out why.. :P
reviews.reviewText: Edit - *from 4 stars to 3* - The more time that goes on, the more I hate these, they are a major reason that prevents me from opening my case and moving stuff in it, because they screw ups are just in my face, they are taking up every inch in my case, and I have a huge case, especially when you're running two graphics cards and lots of hard-drives.. I don't recommend these at all, unless you absolutely need them for whatever reason. Just go for full PSU cables, extensions SU CK!! I'm sorry.Been waiting for tooo long to write this review. Had the things for like 3 months, worked with them a lot.And oh god... are they hard to work with, but are great to look at. They were the biggest pain to work with.First things first..Pros: - Stiff, rugged, durable. - So beautiful.Cons: - TOO stiff, to the point where you almost can't bend them around and make tight turns in your case, they just... physically won't. Let me explain, the two rows of lines in the 24pin for example, both rows are the exact same length, and are very very thick and stiff, so there really isn't much room to wiggle them and move them around. If you bend the 24pin to a circle shape, the cable feels like it's gonna break... just really hard to work with. - This isn't really a con because I should've known better, but those are extensions, not stand alone power cables, they are all short, which means more cables in your case to hide and deal with, would've been much more convenient if they were full length stand alone cables, but that's practically my fault for not looking carefully into descriptions and reviews.All in all, now that I'm done working with them, and all I do is looking at them!?? I love them so much!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 7, 2019
reviews.reviewText: They are just extensions but they look great and are easy to install. It motivated me to get my wiring all cleaned up lolThe price is decent. I would say expensive for JUST extensions BUT saved me a few dollars in comparison to actual cables with different colored material around 'em.A plus is the fact that you get a whole set of wires instead of paying $40 for just one 8pin (pretty ridiculous!)

reviews.reviewTitle: Thermaltake TtMod Kit de cable de alimentación de extensión
reviews.reviewText: Desde que compré las extensiones a día de hoy ha pasado suficiente tiempo y no han fallado en nada y ni me han ocasionado comportamientos raros en la energía suministrada de la fuente de poder a la motherboard o a la gpu.
Get this product after long time..order it now if you gonna use this product after 2 months

reviews.reviewTitle: These will make you look sexy.
reviews.reviewText: If you have a Semi or Non Modular PSU, then these are for you! Bought them, they ship fast and come in great packaging. And the cable them selves look sexy, comes with cable combs, easy to use, and are overall high quality! I recommend!

Si estás armando una pc con una gabinete donde luzca el interior, sin lugar a dudas debes usar este tipo de cable, hace lucir mucho tu computadora y son muy resistentes y flexibles, en mi caso tengo un gabinete Antec Torque y al ser negro con rojo, compré los cables del mismo color y quedó de lujo. Además de que traen agarraderas para peinar los cables y que se luzcan todavía mejor, el largo es bastante bueno. Si tu gabinete es cerrado no vale la pena usarlos
